<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 96-08-06 - Engine Fan Continuously Runs</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi960806" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>96-08-06</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>September, 1996</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ELECTRICAL</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Engine Fan Continuously Runs</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Horton</vendor>
                <vendor>Kysor</vendor>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to all models with 1994 or later Detroit Diesel and Caterpillar electronic
                    engines with air conditioning and Horton or Kysor fans, and all Cummins CELECT Plus engines built
                    after November 1995 with air conditioning and Horton or Kysor fans.
                </para>
                <para>On vehicles with the above listed engines with air conditioning, the proper refrigerant switch
                    must be used. In the above applications, the refrigerant switch does not directly control the fan
                    solenoid, it provides a signal to the engine Electronic Control Module (ECM) which in turn controls
                    the fan solenoid. The refrigerant switch used to provide the signal to the ECM must have gold
                    internal contacts.
                </para>
                <para>Note that the pressure settings between the gold and non-gold contact switches are different and
                    the gold contact switch must only be used in applications listed above. Using the gold contact
                    switch in applications not listed above will cause excessive fan cycling.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
